<?php $vector = is_array($data['test_vector'] ?? null) ? $data['test_vector'] : []; ?>
<header class="page-hero"><div class="shell page-hero-inner"><p class="eyebrow">Server-authoritative play</p><h1>Outcome verification</h1><p class="lede">Completed committed rounds reveal a rotated server seed so their documented random stream can be independently reproduced. A current secret seed is never exposed.</p></div></header>
<section class="section shell article-layout"><nav class="article-nav" aria-label="On this page"><a href="#verify">Verify a seed</a><a href="#method">How it works</a><a href="#limits">What this proves</a></nav><article class="prose"><h2 id="verify">Reproduce a committed stream</h2><?php if(!empty($data['error'])): ?><div class="notice notice-error" role="alert"><?= e((string)$data['error']) ?></div><?php endif; ?><?php if(is_array($data['values'] ?? null)): ?><div class="callout callout-gold"><strong>Generated values:</strong> <?= e(implode(', ', $data['values'])) ?></div><?php endif; ?><form method="post" class="form-stack" action="<?= route('fairness.check') ?>"><?= csrf_field() ?><label class="field"><span>Published server-seed hash</span><input name="server_seed_hash" required minlength="64" maxlength="64" value="<?= e((string)($vector['serverSeedHash'] ?? '')) ?>"></label><label class="field"><span>Revealed server seed</span><input name="server_seed" required maxlength="191" value="<?= e((string)($vector['serverSeed'] ?? '')) ?>"></label><label class="field"><span>Client seed</span><input name="client_seed" required maxlength="128" value="<?= e((string)($vector['clientSeed'] ?? '')) ?>"></label><div class="form-grid"><label class="field"><span>Nonce</span><input name="nonce" type="number" min="0" value="<?= e((string)($vector['nonce'] ?? 0)) ?>"></label><label class="field"><span>Minimum</span><input name="minimum" type="number" value="0"></label><label class="field"><span>Maximum</span><input name="maximum" type="number" value="36"></label><label class="field"><span>Values</span><input name="count" type="number" min="1" max="100" value="10"></label></div><button class="button button-gold" type="submit">Verify and reproduce</button></form><h2 id="method">How it works</h2><p>Before a round, the server publishes SHA-256 of an unpredictable server seed. Outcomes use an HMAC-SHA-256 stream combining that unrevealed seed, your client seed, and a nonce. Once the round is complete, the rotated seed is revealed and can be checked against the earlier hash.</p><h2 id="limits">What this proves</h2><p>A match shows that the revealed seed corresponds to its earlier commitment and that the documented stream is reproducible. It does not prove perfect randomness, predict future rounds, or give virtual currency any cash value.</p></article></section>
